definition.value: A methyl mannoside having alpha-configuration at the anomeric centre.
A 1,1-bis(phosphonic acid) consisting of methane substituted by two phosphonic acid groups.
A non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is L-glutamine substituted by a methyl group at position 2.
A  tricarboxylic acid amide that is a Good's buffer substance, pKa = 6.6 at 20 degreeC.

A member of the class of azetidines that is (2S)-azetidine 2-carboxylic acid in which the carboxylic acid has been converted to the amide corresponding to formal condensation with 4-(aminomethyl)benzenecarboximidamide and in which the hydrogen attached to the azetidine nitrogen is replaced by a (2R)-2-cyclohexyl-2-[(carboxymethyl)amino]acetyl group.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate having N,N-dimethylguanine as the nucleobase.

A carbapenemcarboxylic acid in which the azetidine and pyrroline rings carry 1-hydroxymethyl and in which the azetidine and pyrroline rings carry 1-hydroxymethyl and 5-(dimethylcarbamoyl)pyrrolidin-3-ylthio substituents respectively.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate having 7-methyl-7,8-dihydroguanine as the nucleobase.
An L-alpha-amino acid, methionine, with the S-methyl group trifluoro-substituted.
A phenylalanine derivative consisting of L-phenylalanine having a methyl substuent attached to the alpha-amino function.
The S stereoisomer of alpha-phenylglycine.
A leucine derivative obtained by replacement of one of the amino hydrogens of leucine by a methyl group.
A  purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is adenosine 5'-monophosphate substituted on N-6 by geminal methyl groups.
A hydrazone obtained by formal condensation of the two carbonyl groups of methylglyoxal with the primary amino groups of two molecules of aminoguanidine.
An L-lysine derivative comprising L-lysine having two methyl substituents attached to the side-chain amino group.
A methyl-L-methionine having the methyl group attached to the alpha-amino function.
A primary alcohol that is heptane which is substituted by a methyl group at position 6 and a hydroxy group at position 1.
A menaquinone whose side-chain contains 8 isoprene units in an all-trans-configuration.
A monosaccharide derivative that is the 3-O-methyl derivative of alpha-L-rhamnopyranose. An epitope identified from the glycolipids isolated from Mycobacterium peregrinum.
Monophosphorylated isopropyl alcohol.
A hydroxyimidazole that has an imidazole core with carboxymethyl, 1-aminoethyl, methyl and hydroxy groups at the 1-, 2-, 4- and 5-positions respectively (the S enantiomer).
A molybdopterin that is the O-phospho derivative of [(5aR,8R,9aR)-2-amino-4-oxo-6,7-disulfanyl-3,5,5a,8,9a,10-hexahydro-4H-pyrano[3,2-g]pteridin-8-yl]methanol.
The methyl ester of L-leucine.
An N-methyl-L-asparagine with a single methyl substituent attached to the amide nitrogen.
